               , which implies an expected lifetime horizon of 67 years. The population growth rate is set to 1.3%. This means that aggregate dividend income and labor income grow at 1.3%. The population growth rate has declined in recent years, although here it is also used to control the percentage of population in each stage of their lives. We conduct some sensitivity analysis on this variable. We set
